@* Random -> __rnd (BENCH n°63, decision 146): TWO regimes behind one emitted factory.

   SEEDED `new Random(42)` is deterministic and PROVABLE: .NET's seeded Random is the Knuth
   subtractive generator (Net5CompatSeedImpl, stable by compat guarantee), reimplemented exactly in
   the emitted __rnd(seed) -- so Blazor renders the REAL BCL's sequence, Filament renders the JS
   sequence, and the oracle's byte-equality on #out IS the faithfulness proof against the BCL itself.

   UNSEEDED Random.Shared is arbitrary on BOTH sides (C#'s xoshiro is not reproducible across runs
   either): Math.random behind the same interface, measured with a RANGE predicate on #pick.

   DOM contract: #out starts "0"; each #roll adds rng.Next(1, 7) -- a die -- so three clicks render
   the exact seeded sum on both sides. #pick starts "-1"; #shared stores Random.Shared.Next(10),
   asserted in [0, 10). *@

<p><span id="out">@sum</span></p>
<p><span id="pick">@last</span></p>

<button id="roll" @onclick="Roll">roll</button>
<button id="shared" @onclick="Pick">pick</button>

@code {
    private System.Random rng = new System.Random(42);
    private int sum = 0;
    private int last = -1;

    private void Roll()
    {
        sum += rng.Next(1, 7);
    }

    private void Pick()
    {
        last = System.Random.Shared.Next(10);
    }
}
